==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adhibit
<hw>Ad*hib"it</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adhibitus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>adhibere</ets> to hold to;
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>habere</ets> to have.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
admit, as a person or thing; to take in.</def>
<rj><au>Muirhead.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To use or apply; to administer.</def>
<rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To attach; to affix.</def>
<rj><au>Alison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adhibition</ent>⟦br⟧
